# ErsatzTV Legacy Data Formats

Target **ErsatzTV Legacy** M3U + XMLTV output first. Sample files: `cursor_dev_files/sample_resources/`.

## M3U (`channels.m3u`)

- Header: `#EXTM3U` with `url-tvg` / `x-tvg-url` pointing at the XMLTV URL.
- Each channel = `#EXTINF` line + URL line on the next line.
- Key EXTINF attributes (parse all; some channels use decimal numbers like `57.5`):
  - `tvg-id` — **join key** to XMLTV `<channel id>` and `<programme channel>`
  - `tvg-chno` / `channel-number` — display/sort channel number
  - `tvg-name` — short name; display name also appears after the comma
  - `tvg-logo` — channel logo URL
  - `group-title` — category (e.g. "Nostalgia Networks", "24/7 TV Shows")
  - `channel-id` / `CUID` — ErsatzTV internal IDs (optional for UI)
- Stream URL: HTTP(S) `.ts` endpoint (e.g. `…/iptv/channel/3.ts`).

```text
#EXTINF:0 tvg-id="C3.147.ersatztv.org" tvg-chno="3" tvg-name="UPN" …, UPN
https://example/iptv/channel/3.ts
```

## XMLTV (`xmltv.xml`)

- Root: `<tv generator-info-name="ersatztv">` — often **minified** (few newlines); use a streaming XML parser (`QXmlStreamReader`), not line-based parsing.
- `<channel id="…">` — `id` matches M3U `tvg-id`.
  - Multiple `<display-name>` entries (number + name variants).
  - `<icon src="…"/>` for logo.
- `<programme start="…" stop="…" channel="…">`:
  - Times: `YYYYMMDDhhmmss ±ZZZZ` (e.g. `20260611034350 -0700`).
  - `<title>`, optional `<sub-title>`, `<desc>` (HTML entities like `&#39;`).
  - `<category lang="en">` — multiple genres.
  - `<icon src="…"/>` and `<image type="poster" …>` for artwork.

## Backend design notes

- Fetch M3U + XMLTV via `QNetworkAccessManager` (see `PlexBackend` patterns).
- Cache parsed results in the data dir; refresh on demand or via a manifest `action` setting.
- Join channels ↔ programmes on `tvg-id` / `channel id`.
- Sort channels by numeric `tvg-chno` (parse as `double` for values like `201.2`).
- EPG URL: read from M3U header `url-tvg` when present; allow override in settings.
- For local dev, support `file://` paths to `cursor_dev_files/sample_resources/`.

## Settings gap

Existing manifest types have no URL/text field. Options:
1. Add a `text` setting type to the shell (preferred for M3U/EPG URLs), or
2. Use `directory_browser` for local file paths during development only.

Do not assume generic IPTV M3U/XMLTV dialects until ErsatzTV passes.
